ComicInfo.Title: Charlie Jr.; The Last Past Master and the Late Great Kate; Sex Isn't Everything; All-God Comix; How Jesus Fed the Five (count 'em) Five Thousand.; Worker Ant the Proletarian; B. B. Bush, Man of the World Meets Puss 'N Boots; Scenes From Contemporary Life; Kristy Menstrual Undercover Waitress; Man of the World Discusses the Facts of Life!!; The Left-Overs; Bud Pud The Nark Next Door; Duck and Weevil; The Point Head Cafe; Automatic Transmission; Four More Years; The Sunday Bogeyman Times; What Does He Know; Annie Rat; Manuel Dexterity Goes to Town
ComicInfo.Summary:
Uncle Wollo comes home to find Kate's corpse taken by his nephew.
A tribesman chases down the end of a rainbow.
Jesus goes to San Francisco to convert hippies.
Worker Ant wakes up for the daily grind.
Bernard's and the neighbor's cat get it on.
The Road Vultures motorcycle gang "reprimand" the Eden brothers and companion outside the Signet Lounge on March 3, 1963.
Kristy poses as a waitress to get material for her book.
Hitchhiking with handmade road signs.
Getting hit by a bus.
Mr. Know-It-All is bewildered that Nixon won the election. He provokes the ire of a plainclothes policeman.
Three four-panel strips.
A leper wants to be healed.
Annie does fellatio.
Manuel sees the Sheriff.
